<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-02-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-02-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="1487" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1487">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.41/105.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Edwards</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Ciudad Juarez</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-02-22">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 22, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department’s February 21. Request for the body of William Benton was
                                made by me during interview of the evening of nineteenth. Villa said
                                he could not let the body go now but would do so later. He was then
                                requested as a favor to me to mark well the grave. This he promised
                                to have done. Will make another attempt to secure the body.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwards</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>